AAd.caption: Selected fields
AAd.doc: if you want in json only certain fields in the bubble object to select, the enumerations
AAd.name: selectedFields

AAf.caption: File Name
AAf.doc: Give the JSON file a name
AAf.name: file_name

AAi.caption: Key
AAi.doc: This is the field name the constraint applies to. You can also use the reserved key _all for a full-text search in the database.
AAi.name: key

AAj.caption: Constraint Type
AAj.doc: This is the type of constraint you want to apply. Documentation:https://bubble.io/reference#API.get_api.search_call
AAj.name: constraint_type
AAj.options: equals,not equal,is_empty,is_not_empty,text contains,not text contains,greater than,less than,in,not in,contains,not contains,empty,not empty,geographic_search

AAk.caption: Value
AAk.doc: This is the value the constraint should compare to. It can be a string, number, list, etc.
AAk.name: value

AAm.caption: Origin address
AAm.doc: The central address that defines the center of the search, which should be a string address.
AAm.name: origin_address

AAn.caption: Range
AAn.doc: The range of the radius, defined in miles or kilometers, depending on the unit.
AAn.name: range

AAo.caption: Unit
AAo.doc: The unit to use for the search. It can be miles (default) or km.
AAo.name: unit

AAs.caption: Sort field
AAs.doc: Specify the field to use for sorting.
AAs.name: sort_field

AAt.caption: Descending
AAt.doc: This parameter can either be true or false (default).
AAt.name: descending
